parameters:
\nc<>You've really become strong, senpai. You're like a
different person.
\nc<>You shouldn't underestimate the power of encouragement.

\nc<>What's wrong? Aren't you going to deliver the finishing
blow?

\nc<>Come on, hurry up and kill me to save the two of them,
senpai.
\nc<>Shut up, let me do as I please.

\nc<>Geez, everyone is so selfish, saying 'kill me, kill
me'...!
\nc<>The one who won is me, right?!

\nc<>Senpai risked their life to chase after Candy and Sherbet,
right?
\nc<>No, you're right, but that's not all. I...,

\nc<>I chased after you because I didn't want you to become a
murderer...!

\nc<>What's with that face? Did you think I would hate you just
because you became a villain?

\nc<>You think I would hate you just because you did something
terrible to Candy and Sherbet?

\nc<>There's no way that's true! You're already... and, my
friend! If you try to do something bad, I'll stop you even
if I have to hit you!
\nc<>I didn't mean for you to grab it with your hand like that.
\nc<>So tell me, why did you do something like this?

\nc<>Why did you hide the fact that you are Lilith and approach
me? Why did you give the villains dark power?

\nc<>Why... did you pretend to kidnap Candy and Sherbet when you
had no intention of hurting them...?

\nc<>At first, I was seriously confused, but after calming down
and thinking about it, I understood.

\nc<>There is no need for both of them to be there if it's just
to use them as hostages.

\nc<>I wonder... It's possible that an ordinary citizen wouldn't
become a hostage, so wouldn't it make more sense to capture
Candy and Sherbet, who are close to you, Senpai?

\nc<>That's not it. It's not like we need two hostages or
anything.

\nc<>If I do that, I can also show that I'm not just pretending
to be strong.
\nc<>Huh, what's with that idea? It's scary.

\nc<>If you need the power of a magical girl, it would be much
better to use my power.
\nc<>I understood when I thought about it. Lilith,
\nc<>Reina, you didn't intend to hurt those girls, right?

\nc<>I worked so hard to do a villain-like job, but with this,
I'm disqualified as a demon.
\nc<>Did you feel like talking to me?

\nc<>There's no point in hiding it when it's already been
exposed.
Why did I do something like this?

\nc<>Hmm... to summarize in a few words, I guess it's because I
wanted to see Senpai's true intentions.

\nc<>If I suddenly say that I want to fight, Senpai will probably
go easy on me as usual.

\nc<>That's not true. I am stronger when I fight to protect
rather than when I fight to kill.
\nc<>Anyway, I ended up losing to such a Senpai.
\nc<>The reason I observed Senpai in that way...

\nc<>Hmm, rather than explaining it in words, it would be better
to show it directly.
\nc<>I obtained the memory R5: The Truth of the Town.

\nc<>Good listeners increased by 7,000, while bad listeners
increased by 3,000.
